CSS depends on which factors : cascading, specificity, inheritance.
What is Cascading ?  : An algorithm for solving conflicts where multiple CSS rules applies to an HTML element.
3 types of CSS : Inline, Internal, External
CSS properties are applied where inline has highest specificity. Internal and External specificity is decided by top to bottom approach.
What are selectors ? : Way to target HTML elements and apply CSS properties to it.
element : p, h1, img.......
id : #idname
class : .classname
group selectors : h1,p { property: value}     .container .box{ property: value }
line-height : 9px // 9 px gap between 2 lines






